subsection.def:
the Tunnel Link (隧道及連接道路) means the structure comprising the tunnel and the road within
                the tunnel area connecting the tunnel to Discovery Bay and Siu Ho Wan
                respectively;

subparagraph.content:
carry out any work necessary for the operation, maintenance and repair
                        of the Tunnel Link and other works, facilities or utilities referred to in
                        subparagraph (ii);

paragraph.content:
6 months or part thereof, in the case of the royalty payable under
                    subsections (1)
                    and (2)(a);

he may require a driver to furnish the name and address of the registered
                    owner of the vehicle being driven by him where that information is within his
                    knowledge;

he may require any person whom a tunnel officer reasonably believes to have
                    witnessed any accident or the commission of an offence, to furnish to him his
                    name and address;

the licence is not displayed on an electronic device through an electronic
                    platform specified under section 110A(1)(c) of the Road Traffic
                    Ordinance (Cap. 374);

the licence cannot be read or scanned by the tunnel officer because of a
                    defect of the electronic device on which the licence is purportedly displayed;
                    or

subsection.def:
driver (司機), in
                relation to a motor vehicle, means a person who is in charge of or assisting in the
                control of the vehicle;

